WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:01.653
.

00:01.697 --> 00:03.786
- Previously
on "Good Girls"...

00:03.829 --> 00:05.396
- I don't know what you've

00:05.440 --> 00:06.832
gotten me involved in
but it's something super shady.

00:06.876 --> 00:08.878
- What do you want?
- She's blackmailing us.

00:08.921 --> 00:11.489
- To the tune of $10,000.

00:11.533 --> 00:13.317
- We're gonna be shutting
things down for a while.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.450
- How long?
- I don't know.

00:15.493 --> 00:16.538
- What about us?

00:16.581 --> 00:18.322
- I guess we go legit
for a while.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.846
- Welcome to Dandy Donuts.
What can I get for you?

00:20.890 --> 00:22.500
- I would suggest
that we put Sara

00:22.544 --> 00:23.980
on a list for a transplant.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.155
- Who the hell are you?

00:25.199 --> 00:26.678
- I'm a friend
of your friend's.

00:26.722 --> 00:28.854
- What's that?
- It's that fool we arrested.

00:28.898 --> 00:30.813
He's ours now.
- They have him.

00:30.856 --> 00:32.119
The FBI, and he's talking.

00:32.162 --> 00:33.642
He is talking to them.

00:33.685 --> 00:36.210
- We have to tell Rio.
- If we tell him,

00:36.253 --> 00:37.733
he'll kill him.

00:37.776 --> 00:39.604
- It's that kid or us.

00:41.258 --> 00:43.695
- Tag, you're it!
- Tag!

00:43.739 --> 00:45.958
[soft music]

00:46.002 --> 00:48.178
- So, we're murderers now?

00:48.222 --> 00:51.355
- Yeah, straight up execution
is what it is.

00:51.399 --> 00:52.704
- Cold-blooded killing
of a man.

00:52.748 --> 00:53.705
- His name is Eddy.

00:53.749 --> 00:54.924
He likes his mom,

00:54.967 --> 00:57.057
vintage watches,
and Mexican food.

00:58.145 --> 01:01.104
What, I'm just trying to,
like, humanize him before we--

01:01.148 --> 01:03.324
- We're not killing anyone.
- What do you call it then?

01:03.367 --> 01:04.716
- We're just telling
a gangbanger

01:04.760 --> 01:06.196
that his boy's been flipped
by the cops.

01:06.240 --> 01:07.545
- Yeah, and you know
they're not

01:07.589 --> 01:09.069
going to couples therapy
to work it out.

01:09.112 --> 01:10.113
- The second we open
our mouths--

01:10.157 --> 01:11.419
- You just want to sit here

01:11.462 --> 01:13.899
and let him tell the FBI
all about us?

01:13.943 --> 01:15.858
We're looking at 20 or more,

01:15.901 --> 01:17.773
and I'm not doing that.

01:19.731 --> 01:22.778
[children chattering]

01:25.955 --> 01:27.739
- [laughing] You're it.

01:27.783 --> 01:30.264
[children laughing]

01:33.223 --> 01:35.182
- Let me just say...

01:35.965 --> 01:38.315
It's one thing
to wash fake cash

01:38.359 --> 01:41.101
or rob a grocery store.

01:41.144 --> 01:44.321
But there is a line here,
and if you cross it,

01:44.365 --> 01:46.628
you can't come back.

01:52.547 --> 01:54.592
- Then we don't come back.

02:05.342 --> 02:08.171
- Have yourself a Dandy day.
- Thanks. You too.

02:08.215 --> 02:09.781
- Welcome to Dandy Donuts.

02:09.825 --> 02:11.392
What can I do for you
on this Dandy day?

02:11.435 --> 02:12.958
- [muffled chatter]

02:13.002 --> 02:15.265
- Two decafs
and a glaze please!

02:15.309 --> 02:17.441
- Stepping it up.
- Yeah, thanks.

02:17.485 --> 02:20.227
- You know, I think you're
ready for the night shift.

02:20.270 --> 02:22.272
It pays an extra
75 cents an hour.

02:22.316 --> 02:24.448
- I have two kids, so.

02:24.492 --> 02:27.582
Can I please get
a large coffee and a glaze?

02:27.625 --> 02:29.584
Come on, pep in
your step, folks!

02:29.627 --> 02:31.063
- Okay, okay.
Here you go.

02:31.107 --> 02:33.283
- Dude, this is a promotion.

02:33.327 --> 02:35.242
[cell phone dings]
- [sighs]

02:36.025 --> 02:38.810
[gasps]
- What!

02:38.854 --> 02:40.986
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

02:41.030 --> 02:42.205
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

02:42.249 --> 02:43.424
- So I take that as a yes?

02:43.467 --> 02:45.904
- [yells excitedly]

02:45.948 --> 02:47.341
- La-ding!
- [gasps]

02:47.384 --> 02:49.386
- [laughs] Bing, I upgraded.

02:49.430 --> 02:51.171
Okay? It's got
the three-day battery,

02:51.214 --> 02:52.868
so it's not gonna
short out on you.

02:52.911 --> 02:54.739
You're not gonna drop
any phone calls unless

02:54.783 --> 02:56.306
you put that thing in
the toilet bowl or something.

02:56.350 --> 02:58.221
- Do not do that.
- Please don't do that.

02:58.265 --> 03:00.136
- What do I get?
- A hug.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.660
- And you get a very
important job, little money,

03:02.704 --> 03:05.054
because you need to make sure
that your sister

03:05.097 --> 03:06.447
has got this phone, okay?

03:06.490 --> 03:08.057
Because we have
to be able to be reached

03:08.100 --> 03:09.798
by the hospital day or night.

03:09.841 --> 03:12.540
- Can I get Instagram on this?
- Forget Instagram, baby doll.

03:12.583 --> 03:14.846
You got a big ass
healthy kidney coming!

03:14.890 --> 03:16.413
- Top of the list!

03:16.457 --> 03:18.241
- Top of the list!
♪ New kidney, new kidney

03:18.285 --> 03:20.765
- ♪ Top of the list, top, top
- ♪ New kidney, ah, ah

03:20.809 --> 03:23.159
♪ New kidney, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey ♪

03:23.203 --> 03:24.682
- Can I go do my homework?

03:24.726 --> 03:26.249
- Oh, my God, I love you.
You're such a nerd.

03:26.293 --> 03:28.120
Yes, go ahead.
- Go ahead, baby.

03:28.164 --> 03:29.121
- Uh-uh-uh!
- Yeah, but see,

03:29.165 --> 03:30.340
what's going on here?

03:30.384 --> 03:32.516
- Okay. Okay.

03:34.257 --> 03:35.693
- [sighs]

03:37.217 --> 03:39.306
- I mean...
- I know!

03:39.349 --> 03:42.047
- It's happening.
- It's all happening, babe.

03:42.091 --> 03:43.571
- So if this call comes--
- When

03:43.614 --> 03:44.702
the call comes baby, when.

03:44.746 --> 03:46.226
- How are we gonna pay for it?

03:46.269 --> 03:47.662
- Insurance is gonna
cover some.

03:47.705 --> 03:50.752
- It's gonna be
almost 100 Gs out of pocket.

03:50.795 --> 03:53.276
- Hm.

03:53.320 --> 03:55.235
[suck teeth, sighs]

03:55.278 --> 03:56.758
I know.

03:58.150 --> 04:00.022
[sighs loudly]

04:05.767 --> 04:07.377
Have you heard
from corporate yet?

04:07.421 --> 04:09.292
- What?
- No, I'm just saying

04:09.336 --> 04:11.251
it'd be real good if, you know,

04:11.294 --> 04:13.644
you got your business
started back up.

04:13.688 --> 04:16.473
- Yeah.
It would.

04:20.303 --> 04:21.652
- [sighs]

04:23.219 --> 04:24.438
Oh!

04:24.481 --> 04:27.092
Oh, God, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, sorry!

04:27.136 --> 04:28.485
[door shuts]

04:31.358 --> 04:32.576
- What are you
even doing here?

04:32.620 --> 04:33.795
- What are you even doing here?

04:33.838 --> 04:35.971
- I live here.
- I mean, kinda.

04:36.014 --> 04:37.929
- It's--it's my house.

04:37.973 --> 04:40.062
- I mean, kinda.

04:40.105 --> 04:41.716
- How long are you gonna stay?

04:41.759 --> 04:44.762
- How long are you gonna stay?
- Look, just stop, please.

04:46.286 --> 04:48.592
- Sadie is with Greg.

04:48.636 --> 04:50.115
- Oh.

04:50.159 --> 04:53.249
Well, sorry...

04:53.293 --> 04:54.337
That's sucks.
I didn't know.

04:54.381 --> 04:55.860
- Yeah.

04:55.904 --> 04:59.690
And Bethie said I could
stay here until I feel better.

04:59.734 --> 05:01.083
- That's great.
- Mm-hmm.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.432
- Mi casa, su casa.

05:02.476 --> 05:04.478
- Gracias, hermano.

05:06.131 --> 05:09.352
- So how you feeling right now?
- [inhales deeply]

05:09.396 --> 05:11.311
Not so good, Deansie.

05:11.354 --> 05:12.790
[whispers] Settle in.

05:12.834 --> 05:14.314
- Hm.

05:15.402 --> 05:17.012
- Uh-oh.
What happened?

05:17.055 --> 05:19.057
- Oh, nothing, just get some
- We're just having a chat

05:19.101 --> 05:21.538
- quality time together--
- We've got to go.

05:21.582 --> 05:23.235
We've got that thing

05:23.279 --> 05:24.628
- Bye.

05:24.672 --> 05:26.021
- Y'all ready to be back
in business or what?

05:26.064 --> 05:27.501
- What do you have in mind?

05:27.544 --> 05:29.154
- Just need you to go pick up
a truck for me.

05:29.198 --> 05:30.286
- In Canada?
- No.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.461
Right here.

05:31.505 --> 05:33.158
Parked in a garage
off I-75.

05:33.202 --> 05:34.595
- What's in it?

05:34.638 --> 05:36.379
- Yeah, you ain't got
to worry about that.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.773
Just go get it,
and we're good to go.

05:41.079 --> 05:43.908
I thought y'all would be
more excited than this.

05:43.952 --> 05:45.432
But, hey, if you don't need
to get back to work then--

05:45.475 --> 05:46.998
- Oh, we do. We do.

05:47.042 --> 05:48.783
- There's something we need
to talk about though.

05:48.826 --> 05:51.525
- Yeah, uh, none
of us drive stick.

05:53.788 --> 05:56.660
I mean, everything's automatic,
so I just never learned.

05:56.704 --> 05:58.575
I don't know
about you guys, but...

05:58.619 --> 06:00.229
You know what?
It'll be fine.

06:00.272 --> 06:04.755
It's not an 18-wheeler so
problem raised, problem solved.

06:04.799 --> 06:06.366
- Problem not solved though

06:06.409 --> 06:07.628
because there's
the other problem.

06:07.671 --> 06:10.065
- Which is a
much bigger problem.

06:10.108 --> 06:12.197
- Are you bitches trying
to do this or not?

06:12.241 --> 06:16.288
- Hey, we got 99 problems but
this bitch ain't one, okay?

06:16.332 --> 06:18.378
So we're in like Flynn.

06:18.421 --> 06:20.162
Where the keys at?

06:20.205 --> 06:22.469
[upbeat music]

06:22.512 --> 06:23.861
♪

06:23.905 --> 06:25.515
- We're gonna get
pinched the second

06:25.559 --> 06:27.561
we pull that thing
out of that garage.

06:27.604 --> 06:29.084
- Now look who's down
with the lingo.

06:29.127 --> 06:31.173
- There's no way that kid
didn't tell the FBI

06:31.216 --> 06:33.436
about a truckload full
of God knows what.

06:33.480 --> 06:35.003
- And Sara
will literally be

06:35.046 --> 06:36.700
bumped off the list
if we don't get the money.

06:36.744 --> 06:38.572
- Wait, seriously?
- You have to pay up front

06:38.615 --> 06:40.530
before the surgery.
- What?

06:40.574 --> 06:42.532
You can't like finance it
or something?

06:42.576 --> 06:44.708
- It's a kidney,
not a refrigerator.

06:45.753 --> 06:49.234
- All right, this is it.
Up here on the left.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.672
- ♪ We gonna do this

06:51.715 --> 06:53.282
♪ Like, like we do this

06:53.325 --> 06:55.458
♪ Ain't nobody else
can do this ♪

06:55.502 --> 06:57.460
♪ Like us,
like us ♪

06:57.504 --> 06:59.419
♪ Like I can do this

06:59.462 --> 07:00.898
♪ Like, like we do this

07:00.942 --> 07:04.032
♪ Ain't nobody else
can do this... ♪

07:04.075 --> 07:05.642
- There it is.

07:09.516 --> 07:10.952
- I mean, I don't see any cops.

07:10.995 --> 07:12.562
- Yeah but that doesn't mean
they're not around.

07:12.606 --> 07:15.435
[sighs]
- What do you think it's in?

07:15.478 --> 07:17.480
The next shipment of fake cash?

07:17.524 --> 07:20.091
- Bodies.
Dozens maybe.

07:20.135 --> 07:23.312
[snickers] Could be hundreds
if they're chopped up.

07:23.355 --> 07:24.922
- Just give me the keys.
- Now?

07:24.966 --> 07:26.358
- We got to get back
in business.

07:26.402 --> 07:29.013
- Oh, dude, don't do it.
Seriously.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.624
- It's my family.

07:42.026 --> 07:44.202
- Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait.

07:46.814 --> 07:49.425
Maybe we should ask Stan first.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.035
- We?
- Well, you.

07:51.079 --> 07:52.689
- You want me to
ask my cop husband

07:52.733 --> 07:54.561
if his cop friends
have their eye on a truck

07:54.604 --> 07:56.171
that's potentially filled
with dead bodies.

07:56.214 --> 07:58.521
- Well, I would be
a little bit more subtle,

07:58.565 --> 08:00.175
but that's your call.

08:02.264 --> 08:03.744
- [sighs]

08:05.572 --> 08:07.835
- [sighs]

08:08.531 --> 08:09.924
- You okay?

08:09.967 --> 08:11.534
- I mean, just add it
to the list of things

08:11.578 --> 08:12.927
I'm not okay with.

08:12.970 --> 08:14.755
Like taking orders
from grown men

08:14.798 --> 08:17.888
who go by the names of Bullet,
Demon, and Mr. Cisco.

08:17.932 --> 08:20.630
- [gasps] Which one
is Mr. Cisco?

08:21.979 --> 08:23.241
Ew!

08:23.285 --> 08:25.113
- [laughing] You are making
those names up.

08:25.156 --> 08:26.636
- I am not!

08:26.680 --> 08:28.638
I saw the one
with the skull tattoo

08:28.682 --> 08:30.901
call the one
with the grill "Mr. Cisco."

08:30.945 --> 08:32.990
Now, whether that's
a God given name or a nickname

08:33.034 --> 08:35.340
I don't know,
but he answers to it.

08:35.384 --> 08:37.429
- I am truly disturbed.

08:37.473 --> 08:38.909
- Yeah, well get in line.

08:38.953 --> 08:41.259
- Mr. Cisco
is the one to watch.

08:41.303 --> 08:43.479
Mark my words.
[engine turns over]

08:43.523 --> 08:45.176
Nothing but trouble.

08:45.220 --> 08:46.438
- Let's go.

08:46.482 --> 08:47.875
- Please.

08:52.096 --> 08:52.270
.

08:52.314 --> 08:54.534
- Ma'am, did you find
everything okay today?

08:54.577 --> 08:56.187
Where do you guys
hide the baby formula?

08:56.231 --> 08:57.580
Hi, by the way.
[chuckles]

08:57.624 --> 09:00.191
- Uh, it's in aisle six
with the diapers.

09:00.235 --> 09:02.019
- Duh, obvs--hey,
honey, aisle six.

09:02.063 --> 09:03.368
Will you go get some
baby formula?

09:03.412 --> 09:06.154
Okay, but nothing
organic or expensive.

09:06.197 --> 09:08.199
[to baby] A few pesticides
never hurt anybody.

09:08.243 --> 09:10.201
Did they? No, they didn't.
[baby cooing]

09:10.245 --> 09:11.594
Oh, my God, this is so
random, but--

09:11.638 --> 09:13.683
- Can I have this?
- No, no candy.

09:13.727 --> 09:17.078
Um, do you know anything
about hot water heaters?

09:17.121 --> 09:19.907
- They keep your water hot.

09:19.950 --> 09:21.822
- Right, until they get
old and rusty.

09:21.865 --> 09:23.780
[laughing] Right?
- Call the plumber.

09:23.824 --> 09:27.349
- I did, believe me, but the
whole thing cost me 8,000 bucks

09:27.392 --> 09:30.395
plus another 1,500
to dry the carpets.

09:30.439 --> 09:32.572
- We just gave you $10,000.

09:32.615 --> 09:34.965
- What about this?
- One, okay?

09:35.009 --> 09:36.619
- I know.

09:36.663 --> 09:38.926
And I feel so sick about this,
but what am I gonna do?

09:38.969 --> 09:41.798
You know, I got
to feed my kids, right?

09:41.842 --> 09:43.800
- Oh, hell no.

09:43.844 --> 09:46.498
- Oh, come on. I just need
to get through to next month.

09:46.542 --> 09:49.197
- I need a restock
at register three.

09:49.240 --> 09:52.069
Restock at register three.

09:57.161 --> 09:59.424
- So you don't have like
a house account or--

09:59.468 --> 10:01.731
- No.
- Um, how about a

10:01.775 --> 10:05.256
"You Gave Me Counterfeit
Money to Spend" account?

10:05.300 --> 10:06.910
Do you have one of those?

10:06.954 --> 10:10.174
Or a, um, what are
those things called?

10:10.218 --> 10:13.525
Um, an "I Can Still Call
The Cops on You" account.

10:13.569 --> 10:14.701
Maybe? No?

10:14.744 --> 10:16.441
All right, well just put
the whole thing

10:16.485 --> 10:19.270
on the "I'm What's Keeping
You Out of Jail" account.

10:19.314 --> 10:22.622
We'll just--we'll just
call it a day.

10:22.665 --> 10:24.624
Sound good?

10:29.672 --> 10:30.934
[cash register beeps]

10:30.978 --> 10:33.197
You're the best.
Thank you so much.

10:33.241 --> 10:35.025
Don't forget the candy bar.
- I got it. I found it.

10:35.069 --> 10:36.461
- Thanks, honey.

10:36.505 --> 10:38.420
Okay, I said not
organic though.

10:38.463 --> 10:40.944
Eh, it's fine.
It's on sale.

10:40.988 --> 10:43.468
Oh, and I brought
my own bags, so,

10:43.512 --> 10:45.688
you know, that's good
for the environment.

10:45.732 --> 10:46.950
Oh, hey, you.
- Hey.

10:46.994 --> 10:48.256
- How are you?
- Good, how are you?

10:48.299 --> 10:49.692
- Can I hug you at work?
Is that allowed?

10:49.736 --> 10:52.303
- Yeah, that's fine here.
- This is my brood.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.436
Guys, please stay
in the store at least.

10:59.833 --> 11:02.139
- Kids are down.
- Good.

11:02.183 --> 11:04.272
What you got there?

11:08.580 --> 11:10.234
Uh, what is that?

11:10.278 --> 11:12.367
- Leftovers.
- From when?

11:12.410 --> 11:14.674
- Nelly concert, 2003.
- Babe.

11:16.110 --> 11:18.678
I am an officer of the law.
- Off duty.

11:18.721 --> 11:20.462
- I shouldn't even
be seeing that.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.725
