11:49.883 --> 11:51.798
- [sighs] Yeah.

11:52.799 --> 11:56.367
- Haven't we earned
at least one night off?

11:56.411 --> 11:57.847
[sniffs]

11:57.891 --> 12:00.632
- [sniffs, exhales]

12:03.592 --> 12:06.290
Kids are down?
- For the count.

12:06.334 --> 12:08.249
- ♪ You're with a winner
so baby you can't lose ♪

12:08.292 --> 12:09.554
- I can't.
- ♪ I got a secret

12:09.598 --> 12:10.991
♪ Can't leave Cancun

12:11.034 --> 12:12.383
- [shushing]

12:12.427 --> 12:14.864
- It's solid--I mean,
it's solid pine.

12:14.908 --> 12:16.387
And I countersunk the screws.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.259
And these are for paint

12:18.302 --> 12:21.262
or modge-podge or whatever.

12:21.305 --> 12:23.046
What do you think?

12:23.090 --> 12:24.918
- It's really, really nice.

12:24.961 --> 12:26.658
- It's rustic on purpose.

12:26.702 --> 12:30.010
I left it unvarnished
in case you want to, you know,

12:30.053 --> 12:31.925
decoupage or whatever.

12:31.968 --> 12:36.538
- If a bug has six legs it's--
- Disgusting.

12:36.581 --> 12:38.583
- You hate it.
- No, I don't.

12:38.627 --> 12:41.935
I don't.
The woodworking is top notch.

12:41.978 --> 12:45.808
I just think maybe I'm not as
into crafting as I used to be.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.244
- Oh.

12:47.288 --> 12:50.508
Well, it's not only for that.

12:51.379 --> 12:52.902
It's for your stash.

12:52.946 --> 12:54.991
You could put like 1/2 million
bucks in there easy.

12:55.035 --> 12:57.602
That way you don't have to hide
it in the dog food container.

12:57.646 --> 13:00.780
- I don't have a stash anymore.
- Yeah, but you're going to.

13:00.823 --> 13:03.130
Right? Soon.

13:11.921 --> 13:13.401
- I love it.

13:13.444 --> 13:16.534
- You do?
Yes!

13:17.579 --> 13:19.755
- Hey, Kenny, you want
to know a fun bug fact?

13:19.799 --> 13:21.670
- Mm-hmm.
- The girl praying mantis

13:21.713 --> 13:23.585
eats the boy
after they have sex.

13:23.628 --> 13:25.195
- What?
- Oh yeah.

13:25.239 --> 13:30.157
She just bites his weeny
little head right off.

13:32.855 --> 13:35.292
He's so obviously trying
to get back in your pants.

13:35.336 --> 13:37.947
- Please.
- He's using your bathroom.

13:37.991 --> 13:39.166
- He lives here.

13:39.209 --> 13:40.950
- Ugh. Since when?

13:40.994 --> 13:41.995
[water running]

13:42.038 --> 13:44.084
- Since he got cancer.

13:44.127 --> 13:45.650
- Really lucked out
on that one.

13:45.694 --> 13:47.478
[water shuts off]

13:47.522 --> 13:49.437
- Yeah, that's what they call
cancer patients,

13:49.480 --> 13:50.568
the lucky ones.

13:50.612 --> 13:52.962
- You are making
a giant mistake.

13:53.006 --> 13:54.529
- You just slept with your ex.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.357
- Dude, he cheated on you

13:56.400 --> 13:58.011
and almost left you
and your family homeless.

13:58.054 --> 14:00.056
- In the middle
of a custody battle, no less.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.362
- I'm sorry,
but do you remember

14:01.405 --> 14:02.842
what he bought
that little skank?

14:02.885 --> 14:03.886
- Of course I do.

14:03.930 --> 14:05.540
- I'm gonna need you to say it.

14:06.193 --> 14:07.498
- Underwear.
- Nah.

14:07.542 --> 14:09.979
That was not underwear,
baby girl.

14:10.023 --> 14:12.112
That was
bedazzled vagina floss.

14:12.155 --> 14:14.897
Okay? And it was horrible
and humiliating.

14:14.941 --> 14:16.551
And you're starting to forget.
- No, I'm not.

14:16.594 --> 14:17.944
- Then you're starting
to forgive him

14:17.987 --> 14:20.033
which is way worse.
- Let me worry about it.

14:20.076 --> 14:21.556
It's my marriage.

14:23.906 --> 14:25.603
- You can't do both.
- Both what?

14:25.647 --> 14:27.779
- You can't be
this sweet little wifey,

14:27.823 --> 14:31.827
and then also this like
badass criminal boss lady.

14:33.002 --> 14:35.309
- I sound like Carmen Sandiego.

14:35.352 --> 14:37.354
- You should be so cool.

14:38.225 --> 14:39.835
- Can we just go to bed?

14:39.879 --> 14:42.490
- Aw, man, all your drama
made me have to poop.

14:42.533 --> 14:45.623
- Oh, my God.
You have got to go home.

14:45.667 --> 14:48.452
[Nelly's "Hot in Herre"]

14:48.496 --> 14:50.933
♪

14:50.977 --> 14:52.717
♪ Want a little bit
of, ah, ah ♪

14:52.761 --> 14:54.806
♪ And a little bit
of, ah, ah ♪

14:54.850 --> 14:56.939
♪

14:56.983 --> 14:58.245
- Babe.
- Yeah?

14:58.288 --> 14:59.594
- Can you turn it off now?

14:59.637 --> 15:01.639
- Why? I thought you loved it.

15:01.683 --> 15:03.554
- 'Cause if I listen
to it one more time,

15:03.598 --> 15:04.947
I'm gonna need to dance.
- Yeah?

15:04.991 --> 15:07.689
- And I am no condition...
- [laughs]

15:07.732 --> 15:09.952
- To get my groove
on right now.

15:09.996 --> 15:12.346
- No?
- [laughing] No.

15:12.389 --> 15:14.087
- But it's hot in "herre."

15:14.130 --> 15:16.045
Oh, my God.
- [laughs]

15:16.089 --> 15:17.612
- Okay.

15:19.179 --> 15:20.789
[music shuts off]

15:23.618 --> 15:25.576
Hey, you still pack
little money's lunches

15:25.620 --> 15:27.665
with those cheese puffs
in there?

15:27.709 --> 15:30.581
- I like where your head's at.
- He gonna be mad though.

15:30.625 --> 15:32.757
- You could take him.
He's tiny.

15:32.801 --> 15:33.976
- [chuckles]

15:34.020 --> 15:36.239
He is.
- He's so small.

15:36.283 --> 15:39.242
[both laughing]

15:39.286 --> 15:41.810
- Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
but I could also

15:41.853 --> 15:44.378
get the cookie dough
out the fridge, too, though.

15:44.421 --> 15:45.857
- Do it, do it, do it, do it.

15:45.901 --> 15:47.424
- What. Yes.
- Do it. Okay.

15:47.468 --> 15:49.165
- I'm a genius.

15:49.209 --> 15:50.645
Okay.

15:53.039 --> 15:54.954
- [chuckling]

16:05.051 --> 16:07.357
[cell phone ringing]

16:07.401 --> 16:08.793
- What's up?

16:08.837 --> 16:12.319
- I forgot.
- You called me.

16:13.015 --> 16:14.799
- I forgot what I was supposed
to ask Stan.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.279
- Huh?
- Literally.

16:16.323 --> 16:18.325
What am I supposed
to be asking?

16:18.368 --> 16:20.109
- Dude, are you faded?

16:20.153 --> 16:22.938
- I mean, yeah, he gets chatty
when he smokes, so...

16:22.982 --> 16:25.985
- [laughing] Well played.

16:26.028 --> 16:27.943
- So what am I supposed
to be asking?

16:27.987 --> 16:32.121
- If the kid told the cops
about a truck.

16:32.165 --> 16:33.688
- Right.

16:33.731 --> 16:35.081
- Okay.

16:36.691 --> 16:38.084
- I mean, can you just do it?

16:38.127 --> 16:40.912
- What? No.
- I can put you on speaker.

16:40.956 --> 16:43.089
- Trust me.
That would be super weird.

16:43.132 --> 16:46.309
- It doesn't seem that weird.
- Just slip it in there.

16:46.353 --> 16:48.355
You know, real cas'.
No big deal.

16:48.398 --> 16:50.879
- Okay, okay.
Okay.

16:53.055 --> 16:54.578
- [chuckles]

16:54.622 --> 16:56.015
[footsteps approaching]

17:02.108 --> 17:03.587
- Hey, babe.

17:03.631 --> 17:06.895
So that gangster kid
that you all flipped,

17:06.938 --> 17:09.898
did he say something
about a truck or something?

17:17.993 --> 17:19.777
- A'ight so

17:19.821 --> 17:22.084
we sit this kid down, right.

17:22.128 --> 17:24.391
And before we can even start,

17:24.434 --> 17:25.653
my man's acting like
he's about to get

17:25.696 --> 17:27.176
water-boarded
or something like that.

17:27.220 --> 17:28.482
Starts singing like a bird.

17:28.525 --> 17:30.223
- For real?
- Yes.

17:30.266 --> 17:31.702
Talking about places,

17:31.746 --> 17:34.618
time, faces.
- Stop.

17:34.662 --> 17:36.359
- Names.
- Trucks?

17:36.403 --> 17:38.100
- What?

17:38.144 --> 17:39.710
All kinds of stuff.

17:43.105 --> 17:43.540
.

17:43.584 --> 17:45.586
- Tyler.
You got a sec?

17:45.629 --> 17:48.415
- Oh, I'm technically on break
for three more minutes.

17:48.458 --> 17:49.851
- Well, I don't think

17:49.894 --> 17:51.592
you're gonna want
to wait to hear this.

17:51.635 --> 17:53.028
- Am I getting a Segway?

17:53.072 --> 17:56.336
- No. No, this is not
about a pursuit vehicle.

17:56.379 --> 17:57.815
- Um.

17:57.859 --> 18:00.122
Is it about the hamburger meat?

18:00.166 --> 18:01.776
- I'm making you employee
of the month.

18:01.819 --> 18:03.169
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

18:03.212 --> 18:04.561
Well, not this month,

18:04.605 --> 18:06.085
but I'm putting you
on the fast track.

18:06.128 --> 18:09.088
- Thank you, Mr. Petersen.
- Eh, come on.

18:09.131 --> 18:10.654
Call me Leslie.

18:10.698 --> 18:13.135
- Yes, sir, Leslie.
- Rolls right off the tongue.

18:13.179 --> 18:14.354
- Uh-huh.

18:14.397 --> 18:17.313
- [exhales] Hey, you know, um,

18:17.357 --> 18:19.620
I saw you were
helping a lady out

18:19.663 --> 18:20.882
at Annie's register
the other day.

18:20.925 --> 18:22.188
You know, you gave her a hug?

18:22.231 --> 18:23.841
- Oh, she initiated contact.

18:23.885 --> 18:26.235
Plus I know her.
- Oh, it's okay.

18:26.279 --> 18:30.021
No, I was just wondering
did you, um,

18:30.065 --> 18:31.545
meet her on the job?

18:31.588 --> 18:34.113
- No, not this job.
Mary Pat's from my side job.

18:34.156 --> 18:35.418
- Mm?
- Yeah.

18:35.462 --> 18:37.855
- Oh, what's the side job?

18:41.511 --> 18:43.426
You know, it doesn't matter.
[clears throat]

18:43.470 --> 18:45.907
I mean, the only reason
I was asking was

18:45.950 --> 18:49.171
because Ms. Mary Pat left
her club card behind.

18:49.215 --> 18:50.781
So I just didn't want her
to miss out on any

18:50.825 --> 18:52.392
Twofer Tuesday deals.

18:52.435 --> 18:54.176
- That's really nice of you.

18:55.221 --> 18:56.570
- Hey, um,

18:56.613 --> 18:58.311
you wouldn't have her number,
would you?

18:58.354 --> 19:01.096
- No--but I do follow her
on Instagram.

19:01.140 --> 19:03.229
She mainly posts stuff
about church and her kids.

19:03.272 --> 19:04.534
It's pretty boring.

19:04.578 --> 19:05.883
Hey, so, for employee
of the month,

19:05.927 --> 19:07.929
is there gonna be like
a ceremony?

19:09.800 --> 19:11.715
See you, Leslie.
[chuckles]

19:12.455 --> 19:13.717
- How sure are you?

19:13.761 --> 19:15.589
- Pretty sure.
- No, that's not enough.

19:15.632 --> 19:17.025
I need, like, a percentage.

19:17.068 --> 19:18.200
- 97%.
- Mm.

19:18.244 --> 19:20.289
Almost as accurate as the pill.
- More.

19:20.333 --> 19:21.899
- No, the pill's 99.9%.

19:21.943 --> 19:23.684
- You can't be .1% knocked up.

19:23.727 --> 19:25.773
- Uh-uh, that's if you
take it perfect.

19:25.816 --> 19:28.602
For most people, it's like 91%.

19:28.645 --> 19:30.343
- For you it was zero.

19:30.386 --> 19:31.561
- Okay.

19:31.605 --> 19:32.867
- Look, I'm never
gonna remember

19:32.910 --> 19:34.521
every single thing
that Stan said.

19:34.564 --> 19:35.696
But I think we should
just go for it.

19:35.739 --> 19:37.045
- All right, here's the test.

19:37.088 --> 19:39.221
Do you remember
that you called me?

19:39.265 --> 19:40.614
- Yes.

19:40.657 --> 19:42.355
- Do you remember
that you were so high

19:42.398 --> 19:44.661
you forgot why you got high?

19:47.098 --> 19:48.491
Mm-hmm.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.146
- Look, I'm pretty sure

19:51.190 --> 19:53.844
the cops don't know
anything about a truck.

19:58.588 --> 20:01.635
- All right. [sighs]
Who's gonna drive?

20:01.678 --> 20:03.463
- Let's draw straws?

20:03.506 --> 20:05.247
- I always lose at that.

20:05.291 --> 20:06.466
- So the straws?

20:06.509 --> 20:07.945
- What about
rock paper scissors?

20:07.989 --> 20:09.599
- We can't do that
with three people.

20:09.643 --> 20:10.992
- Why not?

20:11.035 --> 20:12.515
- Basic math.

20:20.349 --> 20:23.309
[French pop music]

20:23.352 --> 20:30.577
♪

20:48.159 --> 20:49.770
- Everybody okay?

20:51.250 --> 20:52.599
- No smokies on my tail.

20:52.642 --> 20:54.253
- Yeah, I'm good.

20:55.166 --> 20:56.820
- You guys, that was so sick.

20:56.864 --> 20:58.213
They should totally make
a movie about us.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.606
- Eh, no thanks.

20:59.649 --> 21:01.172
- Wait, why not?
- Because I'd have to be

21:01.216 --> 21:02.826
the wisecracking
black getaway driver

21:02.870 --> 21:04.872
with one line who dies
five minutes in.

21:04.915 --> 21:06.395
- Eh, true, true.

21:06.874 --> 21:08.049
I'd be the Pacino.

21:08.092 --> 21:10.356
- Oh, you'd so be
the Joe Pesci.

21:10.399 --> 21:11.748
- What?
- Total Pesci.

21:11.792 --> 21:13.097
- Because I'm short?

21:13.141 --> 21:15.099
- It's like a whole Pesci vibe
with you.

21:15.143 --> 21:16.797
- [scoffs] All right,
you know what? Forget it.

21:16.840 --> 21:17.972
The movie's off.

21:18.015 --> 21:20.104
- Guys.
- Pesci vibe.

21:20.148 --> 21:21.323
- Guys.

21:21.367 --> 21:22.759
- What?

21:24.021 --> 21:25.893
- There's a cop behind me.

21:27.416 --> 21:28.591
- Okay.

21:28.635 --> 21:30.158
Okay. Just relax.

21:30.201 --> 21:31.725
- Yeah, that's easy
for you to say.

21:31.768 --> 21:33.248
You're not the one hauling
a truckload

21:33.292 --> 21:34.554
of life sentences here.

21:34.597 --> 21:36.251
- Make a turn.
- Yeah.

21:36.295 --> 21:38.340
Lose that sucker.
- Don't lose him.

21:38.384 --> 21:40.734
Just go slow and chill.

21:40.777 --> 21:43.258
See if he follows.
- Okay.

21:43.302 --> 21:45.434
Okay.

21:45.478 --> 21:48.437
[tense music]

21:48.481 --> 21:54.313
♪

21:54.356 --> 21:57.054
[blinker clicking]

22:08.675 --> 22:10.285
- What's up?

22:10.329 --> 22:11.939
- He's still there.

22:12.940 --> 22:14.550
- Just keep it together.

22:14.594 --> 22:16.683
We got you.
We're here.

22:23.820 --> 22:25.561
- You guys have to help
Dean with the kids.

22:25.605 --> 22:27.911
He can't do it alone.
- Will you stop?

22:27.955 --> 22:29.783
- And I don't want him
marrying a bimbo.

22:29.826 --> 22:31.698
- Oh, he's 100%
gonna marry a bimbo.

22:31.741 --> 22:33.743
- No bimbos around my kids.

22:33.787 --> 22:35.310
- All right, no bimbos.

22:35.354 --> 22:37.225
- Monday's pizza day.
The kids don't need lunch.

22:37.268 --> 22:40.054
Dance Tuesday.
Same as the math tutor.

22:40.097 --> 22:42.143
The dentist appointments
are on the refrigerator.

22:42.186 --> 22:44.319
Trash and recycling
goes out Wednesday.

22:44.363 --> 22:47.366
[police siren whooping]

22:48.367 --> 22:49.716
- What's that?
What's happening?

22:49.759 --> 22:51.239
[sirens wailing]

22:51.282 --> 22:53.328
- Beth? Beth.

22:53.372 --> 22:54.808
Say something.

22:54.851 --> 22:56.287
What's going on?

22:57.811 --> 23:00.683
- I'll write it all down,
but he'll need a village.

23:00.727 --> 23:03.077
[radio chatter]

23:03.556 --> 23:05.296
I got to go.
[phone beeps]

23:16.525 --> 23:17.831
Is there a problem, officer?

23:17.874 --> 23:19.659
- Driver's license
and registration.

23:19.702 --> 23:21.312
- Just give me a minute.

23:22.792 --> 23:24.185
I hope I wasn't speeding.

23:24.228 --> 23:26.927
I've been rushing
around like crazy all day.

23:26.970 --> 23:28.494
- Why's that?

23:28.537 --> 23:30.060
- Um.

23:30.104 --> 23:32.411
Little bit of
a domestic situation.

23:32.454 --> 23:34.195
Not a good guy, you know?

23:34.238 --> 23:36.502
Had to get out of there
as quickly as possible.

23:36.545 --> 23:39.461
#TimeIsUp, am I right?

23:39.505 --> 23:41.028
It's one of those.

23:42.943 --> 23:44.988
- This your truck?
- I borrowed it.

23:45.032 --> 23:48.383
From a friend who's helping me
with the domestic thing.

23:48.427 --> 23:49.863
Am I in trouble here?

23:49.906 --> 23:52.779
- First off, you're driving
without a license plate.

23:52.822 --> 23:55.085
- My friend's a little bit
of a mess too.

23:56.478 --> 23:57.914
- What's her name again?

23:58.611 --> 23:59.960
- Sorry?

24:00.003 --> 24:02.049
- The friend who loaned
you the truck?

24:02.832 --> 24:04.704
- Oh, it's more
of a friend of a friend.

24:04.747 --> 24:07.097
- I need you to get
out of the car.

24:10.536 --> 24:12.276
You got a key to this lock?

24:13.539 --> 24:14.540
[keys jingle]

24:14.583 --> 24:16.542
- It must be one of these.

24:16.585 --> 24:18.282
[jingling lock]

24:26.769 --> 24:27.944
That's weird.

24:27.988 --> 24:29.642
- #TimesUp.

24:29.685 --> 24:36.953
♪

24:56.582 --> 24:56.756
.

24:56.799 --> 24:58.845
All: ♪ Praise him, praise him

24:58.888 --> 25:04.459
♪ Ever in joyful song

25:05.025 --> 25:06.983
- Praise him, indeed.
Amen.

25:07.027 --> 25:08.376
- [whispers] Amen.

25:08.419 --> 25:10.247
- Okay, fellowship
with your neighbors.

25:10.291 --> 25:11.771
See you all next time.

25:11.814 --> 25:13.163
[indistinct chatter]

25:13.207 --> 25:15.209
- Hey! Give me five!

25:15.252 --> 25:16.993
- He's alive!
- [giggles]

25:17.037 --> 25:19.561
- Give me ten!
- He rose again!

25:19.605 --> 25:21.345
[both chuckle]

25:21.389 --> 25:22.608
- You'll like it here.

25:22.651 --> 25:25.175
People are cool,
the choir's strong--

25:25.219 --> 25:27.090
- Most importantly,
how are the donuts?

25:27.134 --> 25:29.484
- Oh, always fresh,
always sprinkled.

25:29.528 --> 25:32.095
- Oh, sold.
[both laugh]

25:33.270 --> 25:38.058
- Well, it was really nice
to meet you, Leslie, and...

25:38.101 --> 25:39.973
you know, you have
a really good voice.

25:40.016 --> 25:42.062
- Oh.
- [chuckles]

25:42.105 --> 25:43.585
[clears throat]

25:43.629 --> 25:47.502
- Uh, would you ever want to...

25:47.546 --> 25:51.114
grab a coffee
or something, ever?

25:52.420 --> 25:53.595
- I can't.
- Oh yeah, no, totally.

25:53.639 --> 25:55.292
I get it, I get it.
- It's not you--

25:55.336 --> 25:56.816
- No, no, no, that's fine.
You don't have to.

25:56.859 --> 25:58.557
I get it totally. All right.
- No, I--it's not--

25:58.600 --> 26:00.297
- Sorry for bothering you.
Have a great night.

26:00.341 --> 26:02.299
- [shouting] My husband's dead.

26:07.827 --> 26:10.003
He passed away six months ago.

26:10.046 --> 26:12.266
Do you think you could come
back closer

26:12.309 --> 26:14.007
so I don't have
to shout about it?

26:14.050 --> 26:16.226
- Oh, yeah.
Sorry.

26:17.706 --> 26:19.099
- [chuckles awkwardly]

26:19.142 --> 26:20.491
Um...

26:20.535 --> 26:22.711
So it's not that
I don't want to go.

26:22.755 --> 26:25.453
I do. I know I should
get back out there.

26:25.496 --> 26:28.064
But I am, you know...

26:28.108 --> 26:30.414
It would just be downhill
from here, so.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.027
- How did he pass?

26:34.070 --> 26:36.072
- Heart attack.

26:36.116 --> 26:37.639
He was, um,

26:37.683 --> 26:39.641
playing water guns
with the kids.

26:39.685 --> 26:42.165
My son thinks that he killed
him 'cause he shot him

26:42.209 --> 26:43.776
in the chest
with a Super Soaker

26:43.819 --> 26:45.647
right before he actually died.

26:45.691 --> 26:46.866
- Oh.

26:48.302 --> 26:50.826
- Told you it was downhill
from here.

26:50.870 --> 26:52.915
- No, no. That...

26:52.959 --> 26:54.656
That was a good story.

26:54.700 --> 26:57.311
- [laughs] Well,
